Dear Sir,

Please find attached the IST 1 to IST 7 questionnaire files along with 
the PR approval workflow details and po_para flags analysis for your 
kind review.

1. PR Approval Workflow

The current system supports up to 3 levels of approval.
In practice, some clients are operating with 2 levels by bypassing Level 
2, indicating that a 2-level approval structure is sufficient for 
standard use.
The approval levels are not customer-configurable at present.
For ASL-based PR, the system supports automatic RFQ generation only.
Automatic PO generation is not available; PO creation remains a separate 
manual step after approval.

2. po_para Flags Analysis

As requested, the po_para table has been reviewed in detail.
It is observed that only 6 columns are used in the PR form, listed 
below:
Manual_IndNo
BudgetQty - Actively used
PRapprovalstatus
Penpodetails
PendingOrderPara
InditemGrp -  - Actively used

A comprehensive column-wise status document (covering all fields in the 
po_para table with classification as Used, Customer-specific, or Unused) 
has been prepared and attached for your reference.
This document also includes recommendations aligned with standard 
SPINRISE implementation practices.

Kindly review the attached documents and provide your feedback for PM 
and CEO approval to proceed with the Development Team.

Thanks & Regards
M MuthuVel

